        <div class="interview-text">
          <h3>Penelope on navigating -4.75 myopia</h3>
          <p class="question">Does having perfect vision mean you perceive the world more accurately?</p>
          <p class="answer" data-hint-image="submission-photos/IMG_2845 - annie hong.jpeg" data-next-section="#section2">
            No, they might take their vision for granted. Then again, everyone takes vision for granted and misses out on the little things.
          </p>
          <p class="question">How do you feel in spaces where you canâ€™t see far ahead?</p>
          <p class="answer" data-hint-image="submission-photos/IMG_2845 - annie hong.jpeg" data-next-section="#section2">
            I try to stay to myself when I can't see. However, it's almost comforting not being able to see everything or anyone as I tend to overthink. It's almost like I feel shrunken in those spaces.
          </p>
           <p class="question">Do you ever feel like your mind sees more clearly than your eyes?</p>
          <p class="answer" data-hint-image="submission-photos/IMG_2845 - annie hong.jpeg" data-next-section="#section2">
           I think depending on how vivid the memory is, is how clear the memory is. Most memories are blurrier than how I saw them. 
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

